From: usb-proxy appliance <usb-proxy@local>
Date: Tue, 24 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] musb: gadget: service pending RX packet on requeue instead of
 flushing

musb_ep_restart() flushes the RX FIFO whenever an OUT request becomes the
head of the queue. If a packet has already been received into the FIFO before
the request was queued -- which happens with gadget drivers that re-queue OUT
requests outside completion context (e.g. raw-gadget servicing reads from user
space), leaving a brief window with no request pending -- that packet is
silently discarded. The host already had it ACKed, so it never resends, and the
transfer deadlocks. On single-buffered PIO controllers (Allwinner sunxi) this
reliably breaks bulk-OUT streams (e.g. the ADB CNXN payload, leaving the device
"offline"); double-buffered/large-FIFO controllers (dwc2/dwc3) happen to hide
it.

Service an already-pending packet (RXPKTRDY) via rxstate() instead of flushing.

This is the proper in-tree counterpart to the out-of-tree musbfix.ko kprobe
workaround; baking it into the kernel removes the vermagic fragility entirely.

Signed-off-by: usb-proxy appliance <usb-proxy@local>
---
 drivers/usb/musb/musb_gadget.c | 18 +++++++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/usb/musb/musb_gadget.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/musb/musb_gadget.c
@@ -1179,9 +1179,21 @@ void musb_ep_restart(struct musb *musb, struct musb_request *req)
 		txstate(musb, req);
 	} else {
 		csr = musb_readw(epio, MUSB_RXCSR);
-		csr |= MUSB_RXCSR_FLUSHFIFO | MUSB_RXCSR_P_WZC_BITS;
-		musb_writew(epio, MUSB_RXCSR, csr);
-		musb_writew(epio, MUSB_RXCSR, csr);
+		/*
+		 * If a packet already arrived into the FIFO before this request
+		 * was queued, don't flush it away -- the host already had it
+		 * ACKed, so flushing silently drops it and stalls the transfer.
+		 * Service it instead.  This is the in-tree counterpart to the
+		 * out-of-tree musbfix.ko workaround; required on single-buffered
+		 * PIO controllers (Allwinner sunxi) for reliable bulk-OUT.
+		 */
+		if (csr & MUSB_RXCSR_RXPKTRDY) {
+			rxstate(musb, req);
+		} else {
+			csr |= MUSB_RXCSR_FLUSHFIFO | MUSB_RXCSR_P_WZC_BITS;
+			musb_writew(epio, MUSB_RXCSR, csr);
+			musb_writew(epio, MUSB_RXCSR, csr);
+		}
 	}
 }
